    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nWhen using the default texlab configuration with\n```lua\nvim.lsp.enable('texlab')\n```\nthe `formatexpr` is not set, so formatting with `gq` does not work correctly. When setting `set formatexpr=v:lua.vim.lsp.formatexpr()` manually, `gq` has no effect. This problem does not happen with other lsp clients, like `lua_ls`.\n\n`latexindent` is installed and when called manually works as expected and returns me the correct formatting.\n\nI also checked with emacs and the [texlab lsp-mode](https://github.com/ROCKTAKEY/lsp-latex), where formatting works correctly using `latexindent`, so I suspect this is not a texlab issue.\n\nNeovim version: 0.12.1\nTexlab version: 5.25.1\nLatexindent version: 3.24.7",
